Check git version with "git --version" on CMD

Set Global Username and Email Address using config
>>git config --global user.name "Vinay Agarwal"
>>git config --global user.email "vinay.dbl1998@gmail.com"

Check Global values with "list"
>>git config --list

For help
>>git help <verb>
or
>>git <verb> --help

To Start Tracking a Folder with Git
First Navigate to the Specified Folder
>>git init

To see the status of the GitRepo
>>git status
#Shows which files have been committed and which have not

To ignore certain files inside the directory which should not be tracked, we create the .gitignore file
>>echo $null >> .gitignore
Now add names of all files that should not be tracked in the text file created(Can use wildcards here like *.proj)

